parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake overheating can cause premature wear of brake shoes, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: high temperature of shoes (up to 600 degrees).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of engine power can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds. The frequent illumination of the check engine light can lead to driver distraction and neglect of necessary repairs.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle experiences a loss of power
